This paper deals with the study of pushdown games with mean-payoff objectives, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several subfields of computer science. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), as the paper deals with formal verification and program analysis, which are central topics in this subfield. The paper also deals with game theory, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper deals with graph theory and algorithms, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with modular strategies, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper deals with pushdown automata, which suggests that it could be classified under cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory).
